WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 388
Chapter 388
(House Bill 1276)
AN ACT concerning
West North Avenue Development Authority – Neighborhood Social Connection
and Development Program – Establishment
(WNADA Neighborhood Social Connection and Development Act)
FOR the purpose of establishing the Neighborhood Social Connection and Development
Program within the West North Avenue Development Authority to provide technical
support and grants to certain organizations to implement programs that foster social
connections and activities in a certain area; authorizing the West North Avenue
Development Authority, in conjunction with the Department of Housing and
Community Development, to use funds from the Continuing the CORE Partnership
Fund to assist with the removal of certain blighted property within a certain area;
and generally relating to the Neighborhood Social Connection and Development
Program in the West North Avenue Development Authority.
BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
Article – Economic Development
